cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) is the most likely category as the paper is about dialog system building and dialog generation, which are core topics in computational linguistics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for domain adaptation in dialog systems.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning, to train the dialog system model.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks as the underlying model for the dialog system.
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with spoken dialog systems, which involve sound processing.
